Technology & Innovation Fellowships

11. Mozilla Fellowship Program
Deadline: To be updated
Focus: Internet health and digital rights
Eligibility: Activists, technologists, researchers
Website: https://foundation.mozilla.org/en/what-we-fund/fellowships/
Duration: 10-month program with stipend

12. Google Research Fellowship
Deadline: To be updated
Focus: Computer science and related fields
Eligibility: PhD students worldwide
Website: https://research.google/outreach/phd-fellowship/
Funding: Full tuition and fees plus stipend

13. IBM PhD Fellowship
Deadline: To be updated
Focus: AI, quantum computing, security
Eligibility: PhD students worldwide
Website: https://www.research.ibm.com/university/awards/fellowships.html
Benefits: Stipend, access to IBM researchers and resources

14. Microsoft Research Fellowship
Deadline: To be updated
Focus: Computer science and engineering
Eligibility: PhD students worldwide
Website:https://www.microsoft.com/en-us/research/academic-program/phd-fellowship/
Funding: Full tuition and fees plus stipend for two years

15. TED Fellows Program
Deadline: To be updated
Focus: Technology, entertainment, design, global issues
Eligibility: Innovators worldwide
Website: https://www.ted.com/participate/ted-fellows-program
Benefits: Participation in TED conference, coaching, networking opportunities

16. Schmidt Science Fellows
Deadline: May 19, 2025 (nominations), July 14, 2025 (applications)
Focus: Interdisciplinary scientific research
Eligibility: Recent PhD graduates in natural sciences
Website: https://schmidtsciencefellows.org/
Funding: $100,000 stipend plus benefits

17. Shuttleworth Foundation Fellowship
Deadline: May 1, 2025/November 1, 2025 (two intakes)
Focus: Open knowledge, open innovation
Eligibility: Social entrepreneurs and innovators
Website: https://www.shuttleworthfoundation.org/fellows/
Funding: Project funding up to $275,000
